FBIS3-30227 "dreeu021_k_94001" FBIS-EEU-94-021 Document Type:Daily Report 1 Feb 1994 CROATIA Granic Denies Allegation of Troops in Bosnia LD3101203794 Zagreb Radio Croatia Network in Serbo-Croatian 1800 GMT 31 Jan 94 LD3101203794 Zagreb Radio Croatia Network Language: Serbo-Croatian Article Type:BFN [Excerpts] A statement on the implementation of Croatian foreign policy was adopted at the end of the 12th session of the Chamber of Counties of the Croatian parliament today. [passage omitted] [Reporter] Commenting on Silajdzic's accusations, Mate Granic said: [begin Granic recording] The accusation that there are 30,000 Croatian soldiers in Bosnia-Herzegovina and that plans are being made to send another 20,000 there is a complete lie. There are no more that 2,000 Croatian volunteers and there are certainly at least two or three times more of those who have come from Islamic countries. [end recording] [passage omitted]
